5
00:00:53,666 --> 00:00:58,458
LAST HEROES

6
00:01:06,500 --> 00:01:13,458
KUNG RAGA VILLAGE

7
00:01:47,125 --> 00:01:48,000
Come on, come on.

8
00:01:50,041 --> 00:01:53,208
Hey. Puek. Chote.

9
00:01:55,333 --> 00:01:57,541
-Hey!
-Yes.

10
00:02:49,875 --> 00:02:51,000
Boontueng.

11
00:02:52,958 --> 00:02:53,791
Hi, Fang.

12
00:02:54,458 --> 00:02:56,583
Giving the elephants a bath this early?

13
00:03:00,333 --> 00:03:01,416
Are you going to harvest the rice?

14
00:03:01,500 --> 00:03:04,583
Yes. Before it all falls.

15
00:03:04,875 --> 00:03:06,708
-Let's go, Soi.
-Yes, Auntie Fang.

16
00:03:08,083 --> 00:03:09,375
Be safe.

17
00:03:09,583 --> 00:03:11,041
Yeah! I'm going to the rice field,

18
00:03:11,166 --> 00:03:12,500
not a minefield. Shit.

19
00:03:14,083 --> 00:03:17,083
-Come on.
-The mahouts are so handsome!

20
00:04:30,583 --> 00:04:31,875
Mom. Dad.

21
00:04:31,958 --> 00:04:34,250
The village chief and the monk
are calling us.

22
00:04:34,333 --> 00:04:35,958
See you at the gathering yard.

23
00:04:43,500 --> 00:04:44,458
Fang!

24
00:04:45,458 --> 00:04:46,333
Saeng!

25
00:04:47,333 --> 00:04:49,916
Fang, are you here?

26
00:04:50,000 --> 00:04:51,000
Hey, Duen.

27
00:04:51,083 --> 00:04:52,416
Fang left a while ago.

28
00:04:52,625 --> 00:04:55,041
-Where did she go?
-To the rice paddy.

29
00:04:56,583 --> 00:04:57,916
Saeng, wake up!

30
00:04:58,583 --> 00:05:01,375
They are heading to the gathering yard.
Why are you still sleeping?

31
00:05:02,166 --> 00:05:03,000
Wake up!

32
00:05:04,625 --> 00:05:06,000
Mom.

33
00:05:06,750 --> 00:05:11,041
Whatever reason they are gathering for
has nothing to do with me.

34
00:05:11,666 --> 00:05:13,250
How could you say that?

35
00:05:13,750 --> 00:05:15,583
Get up and hurry. Come along.

36
00:05:17,208 --> 00:05:18,458
Hurry up!

37
00:05:24,291 --> 00:05:26,541
Hey, Saeng. Aren't you coming?

38
00:05:26,625 --> 00:05:28,333
Yeah. But you go ahead.

39
00:05:28,416 --> 00:05:30,833
Hurry. Let's go. Come on.

40
00:05:32,291 --> 00:05:33,958
What's going on?

41
00:05:34,625 --> 00:05:35,875
I have no idea.

42
00:05:58,333 --> 00:05:59,791
I want to turn this way.

43
00:06:02,625 --> 00:06:05,166
-Are you tired?
-Absolutely.

44
00:06:05,333 --> 00:06:07,833
I didn't ask you, old lady.
I asked Kong over there.

45
00:06:07,916 --> 00:06:08,916
Wow. Old lady?

46
00:06:13,208 --> 00:06:15,791
-Fug.
-Fuck Fug. It's Fang.

47
00:06:16,083 --> 00:06:18,000
There's a gathering in the village.
Hurry up.

48
00:06:18,750 --> 00:06:23,041
Gotta be now? Things are heating up,
and I'm about to have fun.

49
00:06:23,291 --> 00:06:24,458
Soi, let's go.

50
00:06:24,541 --> 00:06:27,000
Soi. Fang. Follow me.

51
00:06:27,333 --> 00:06:31,666
Come on, come on. Run, run.

52
00:06:32,666 --> 00:06:35,166
Auntie Fang, hurry up.

53
00:06:48,625 --> 00:06:50,583
-Hold on.
-Wait for us.

54
00:06:50,666 --> 00:06:51,958
Please wait for us.

55
00:06:52,041 --> 00:06:53,500
Wait for me.

56
00:06:53,666 --> 00:06:55,541
Excuse us.

57
00:06:56,916 --> 00:06:58,500
Excuse me.

58
00:07:00,916 --> 00:07:05,000
Today, I've called for a gathering here

59
00:07:05,958 --> 00:07:08,208
because I would like to ask for volunteers

60
00:07:08,708 --> 00:07:12,000
to go spy on the Munramaeng
in Yasotharavadi City.

61
00:07:13,625 --> 00:07:15,000
I would like to volunteer.

62
00:07:15,083 --> 00:07:17,833
If you go, who will protect our village?

63
00:07:18,083 --> 00:07:21,000
What? If it's not him,
who else would it be?

64
00:07:22,291 --> 00:07:24,583
Those who are proper for this job

65
00:07:24,833 --> 00:07:28,958
need to seem harmless,

66
00:07:29,333 --> 00:07:32,000
so nobody suspects them.

67
00:07:32,458 --> 00:07:35,500
This job is very dangerous.

68
00:07:36,208 --> 00:07:39,083
We need those who are smart

69
00:07:39,625 --> 00:07:41,916
and sharp, specifically.

70
00:07:43,958 --> 00:07:46,208
I'm not one of those people, am I?

71
00:07:47,541 --> 00:07:48,750
I guess not.

72
00:07:58,208 --> 00:08:01,208
Why do we need to spy on them?

73
00:08:02,541 --> 00:08:05,458
I don't see that our village
has anything to do with them.

74
00:08:05,541 --> 00:08:07,125
How does it not?

75
00:08:07,291 --> 00:08:09,041
If they want to attack Asoraya City,

76
00:08:09,833 --> 00:08:13,583
they have to come through
our Kung Raga village.

77
00:08:14,708 --> 00:08:18,666
If now we think only of ourselves
or our comfort,

78
00:08:19,458 --> 00:08:24,458
soon when the threat arrives,
our nation could fall.

79
00:08:25,750 --> 00:08:29,541
We are merely simple farmers.
What can we do to spy on them?

80
00:08:29,625 --> 00:08:31,750
-Yeah.
-Yeah.

81
00:08:31,833 --> 00:08:35,500
If nobody volunteers today,

82
00:08:35,583 --> 00:08:38,875
I would like you all to consider this.

83
00:08:39,291 --> 00:08:43,125
Would you like to live for yourself
day after day,

84
00:08:43,208 --> 00:08:45,833
or try to live for the nation
at least once,

85
00:08:47,500 --> 00:08:50,000
now, while everybody is still here today?

86
00:08:51,125 --> 00:08:53,500
Those who would like to volunteer,
please stay.

87
00:08:54,791 --> 00:08:57,375
Those who would not, go back home.

88
00:08:57,583 --> 00:09:00,333
Let's go.

89
00:09:25,750 --> 00:09:27,166
Nobody volunteers.

90
00:09:27,250 --> 00:09:29,458
Thank you very much, Horm,

91
00:09:29,541 --> 00:09:32,000
for considering volunteering.

92
00:09:39,416 --> 00:09:40,250
Geez.

93
00:09:41,291 --> 00:09:42,708
Acting like he would like
to help our village...

94
00:09:42,791 --> 00:09:45,458
It would be so nice if he died on the job.

95
00:09:47,625 --> 00:09:50,958
Then there would be no homosexuals
in our village.

96
00:09:55,291 --> 00:09:56,750
Lower your voice.

97
00:10:02,250 --> 00:10:03,083
Gon.

98
00:10:06,833 --> 00:10:08,000
What?

99
00:10:08,375 --> 00:10:09,666
Are you going?

100
00:10:12,041 --> 00:10:12,875
Where?

101
00:10:16,208 --> 00:10:18,000
To Yasotharavadi.

102
00:10:29,500 --> 00:10:31,833
This time,

103
00:10:31,916 --> 00:10:35,000
if we don't go,
our village will be razed to the ground.

104
00:10:36,291 --> 00:10:40,958
But if I go and happen to die,
how could I live with my life?

105
00:10:46,750 --> 00:10:48,250
You're quiet because you're confused,
right?

106
00:10:48,583 --> 00:10:49,625
Yes, ma'am.

107
00:10:52,000 --> 00:10:53,333
As for me...

108
00:10:53,750 --> 00:10:55,958
-Are you going?
-No, I'm not.

109
00:10:56,500 --> 00:10:59,125
What did you say that for, then?

110
00:10:59,666 --> 00:11:02,791
-Let's go inside and sleep.
-Yes, ma'am.

111
00:11:04,041 --> 00:11:06,083
Talking to you is like talking to a dog.

112
00:11:06,166 --> 00:11:07,166
Fang, Fang.

113
00:11:10,958 --> 00:11:12,791
What's going on, Boontueng?

114
00:11:12,875 --> 00:11:14,375
I would like to talk to you.

115
00:11:14,458 --> 00:11:15,541
About what?

116
00:11:15,833 --> 00:11:17,958
About going to Yasotharavadi.

117
00:11:21,083 --> 00:11:22,416
Are you going?

118
00:11:23,666 --> 00:11:25,750
-I'm thinking about it.
-Thinking?

119
00:11:25,833 --> 00:11:26,666
Yes, thinking.

120
00:11:28,375 --> 00:11:30,791
Go and think in your home. Go!

121
00:11:31,083 --> 00:11:32,166
Yes, ma'am.

122
00:11:35,458 --> 00:11:36,625
Let's go, Auntie.

123
00:11:37,458 --> 00:11:39,791
-Wait for me.
-Fang.

124
00:11:40,791 --> 00:11:44,708
What? I don't get to sleep now?
What do you want, Horm?

125
00:11:45,125 --> 00:11:46,583
I want to talk to you.

126
00:11:46,791 --> 00:11:48,916
About going to Yasotharavadi, right?

127
00:11:49,000 --> 00:11:50,416
Wow, yes.

128
00:11:51,125 --> 00:11:52,875
But I didn't do it voluntarily.

129
00:11:53,000 --> 00:11:55,000
So why are you standing there?

130
00:11:55,083 --> 00:11:55,916
I fell sleep.

131
00:11:58,166 --> 00:11:59,541
You go!

132
00:11:59,625 --> 00:12:00,458
Where?

133
00:12:00,541 --> 00:12:01,958
Go to sleep. It's late.

134
00:12:06,500 --> 00:12:08,375
It's late, so you go to sleep, Gon.

135
00:12:08,458 --> 00:12:10,458
-And when will you sleep?
-During the day.

136
00:12:10,541 --> 00:12:11,375
I knew it.

137
00:12:12,125 --> 00:12:14,875
Let's get back home.
Or you'll be in trouble.

138
00:12:14,958 --> 00:12:16,500
-With Fang?
-With me!

139
00:12:17,500 --> 00:12:20,791
Damn! I shouldn't have wasted time
with your matters.

140
00:12:20,875 --> 00:12:24,875
Staying home and shaving myself
is better than this.

141
00:12:28,500 --> 00:12:31,166
So, who can I talk to about this?

142
00:12:32,208 --> 00:12:33,833
Ah, Duen.

143
00:12:56,666 --> 00:12:59,041
Duen, I would like to talk to you.

144
00:13:00,375 --> 00:13:01,666
I'm already in bed.

145
00:13:07,208 --> 00:13:10,791
She's surely asleep since she's snoring.

146
00:13:53,041 --> 00:13:55,375
Duen, Duen. That's twice.

147
00:13:56,750 --> 00:13:58,541
I would like to talk to you.

148
00:13:59,750 --> 00:14:02,541
-Mom. Dad.
-Yeah?

149
00:14:02,625 --> 00:14:04,166
Let's get inside.

150
00:14:05,833 --> 00:14:07,875
Just got out here and now you want us
to get inside.

151
00:14:07,958 --> 00:14:11,458
Please be careful.

152
00:14:12,166 --> 00:14:13,625
Going inside again?

153
00:14:17,500 --> 00:14:19,333
So, who can I talk to now?

154
00:14:22,500 --> 00:14:24,416
I would like to talk to you.

155
00:14:32,625 --> 00:14:34,583
Your logic sounds good.

156
00:14:37,166 --> 00:14:39,208
What? What did you say?

157
00:14:40,791 --> 00:14:42,125
Moo moo?

158
00:14:43,291 --> 00:14:44,875
Ah, moo.

159
00:14:45,166 --> 00:14:48,958
Thank you very much. Gotta go.
Now I understand.

160
00:14:51,291 --> 00:14:52,125
It's all gone.

161
00:15:00,375 --> 00:15:01,541
Saeng.

162
00:15:06,583 --> 00:15:10,250
You're a man. You can't be drunk
all the time like this.

163
00:15:10,500 --> 00:15:16,000
Right now, the nation needs men like you
to protect it from enemies.

164
00:15:16,500 --> 00:15:18,458
Mom.

165
00:15:19,291 --> 00:15:23,333
How can someone like me
fight with anybody?

166
00:15:23,416 --> 00:15:25,291
Of course, you can.

167
00:15:25,750 --> 00:15:28,416
I would like to see you fight
like a brave soldier.

168
00:15:30,625 --> 00:15:34,208
Look at Krai. Take him as an example.

169
00:15:34,958 --> 00:15:39,291
You must fight at least once before I die.

170
00:16:05,625 --> 00:16:06,666
Krai.

171
00:16:23,291 --> 00:16:25,791
You came here to see me. What's going on?

172
00:16:28,416 --> 00:16:32,791
I want to know if you will fight
with somebody else.

173
00:16:35,333 --> 00:16:38,000
I haven't decided.

174
00:16:39,666 --> 00:16:41,458
Because I have a concern.

175
00:16:44,041 --> 00:16:46,875
My wife, Kumlai, is in this state,
as you can see.

176
00:16:50,375 --> 00:16:51,666
How can I leave her here?

177
00:16:55,875 --> 00:16:57,791
Yeah, I understand.

178
00:16:59,333 --> 00:17:02,791
But if you decide to go,

179
00:17:02,875 --> 00:17:04,416
please let me know.

180
00:17:06,875 --> 00:17:08,041
I'll leave you now.

181
00:17:12,750 --> 00:17:16,000
ASORAYA CITY

182
00:17:16,375 --> 00:17:20,208
Commander, you pestered me to come
to this meeting. What's the matter?

183
00:17:20,625 --> 00:17:24,708
I was going to have fun
with my beloved wife Jamjureethevee.

184
00:17:26,708 --> 00:17:30,333
Right now is not the time to work.

185
00:17:30,666 --> 00:17:34,333
Why did you have to make it a big deal,
Commander?

186
00:17:34,416 --> 00:17:36,250
None of your business.

187
00:17:38,000 --> 00:17:44,375
Our spies have notified me
that Yasotharavadi wants to attack us

188
00:17:44,666 --> 00:17:50,166
and has sent some spy
inside the inner city, Your Majesty.

189
00:17:51,708 --> 00:17:55,250
You mean, right now, some enemy has
infiltrated here

190
00:17:55,500 --> 00:17:58,750
and might have learned
what is going on here, right?

191
00:17:59,666 --> 00:18:00,583
Yes, Your Majesty.

192
00:18:00,666 --> 00:18:06,833
I believe that such enemies
are just some lies,

193
00:18:06,916 --> 00:18:08,041
Your Majesties.

194
00:18:08,125 --> 00:18:12,500
Commander, are you sure that
Yasotharavadi is coming to attack us?

195
00:18:13,333 --> 00:18:17,000
They promised they would end the war.

196
00:18:17,083 --> 00:18:19,541
I don't think they are coming.

197
00:18:20,208 --> 00:18:22,750
Why? Why?

198
00:18:22,833 --> 00:18:28,041
Why would Governor Anorathaporamintin
betray us

199
00:18:28,125 --> 00:18:31,583
when Yasotharavadi knows very well

200
00:18:31,666 --> 00:18:37,041
how hard it is to attack our city?

201
00:18:37,125 --> 00:18:40,791
The news I received is not a lie.

202
00:18:41,291 --> 00:18:46,000
If we don't prepare an army to defend
ourselves, it will be too late.

203
00:18:46,791 --> 00:18:47,958
Your Majesties.

204
00:18:49,916 --> 00:18:53,666
If it happens,
there's no need to be afraid.

205
00:18:54,416 --> 00:18:57,666
I would just dress to fight
and hold swords,

206
00:18:57,750 --> 00:19:02,500
and all of our brave soldiers would be
ready to rise up to protect Our Majesty.

207
00:19:03,708 --> 00:19:05,250
But I think

208
00:19:05,500 --> 00:19:08,791
we shouldn't underestimate Yasotharavadi,
My Lord.

209
00:19:08,875 --> 00:19:12,416
You know nothing about war.
No need to share your opinion. Understand?

210
00:19:14,416 --> 00:19:17,708
I agree with my beloved wife
Jamjureethevee.

211
00:19:22,166 --> 00:19:24,791
The nation is divided right now.

212
00:19:25,083 --> 00:19:27,541
Whatever you want to do, do it now.

213
00:19:28,291 --> 00:19:29,791
I hope you know what I mean.

214
00:19:30,833 --> 00:19:31,666
I do.

215
00:19:46,458 --> 00:19:48,250
Thank you so much. Thank you.

216
00:20:17,791 --> 00:20:21,458
What did you get from spying
on the village that I sent you to?

217
00:20:22,083 --> 00:20:25,750
We are going to win for sure.
People are not united.

218
00:20:26,000 --> 00:20:27,458
They fight with each other
every single day.

219
00:20:28,416 --> 00:20:31,916
They are divided into groups.
Some are always drunk.

220
00:20:32,458 --> 00:20:36,583
We can easily defeat these people.

221
00:20:38,500 --> 00:20:40,875
Wow. How easy it is!

222
00:20:43,000 --> 00:20:45,291
I agree with you, Commander.

223
00:20:50,541 --> 00:20:51,375
Fang.

224
00:20:52,000 --> 00:20:55,125
Do we have volunteers
to go to Yasotharavadi yet?

225
00:20:55,208 --> 00:20:56,791
Why? Are you volunteering?

226
00:20:57,458 --> 00:20:58,416
Yes.

227
00:20:59,250 --> 00:21:03,500
Once in a lifetime, I would like
to do something for my homeland.

228
00:21:03,833 --> 00:21:04,875
That's right, Auntie Fang.

229
00:21:08,541 --> 00:21:09,833
Yeah. I want to, also.

230
00:21:10,500 --> 00:21:12,208
I have only one concern.

231
00:21:13,000 --> 00:21:14,500
-What is it?
-What is it?

232
00:21:22,666 --> 00:21:25,916
-Fang.
-Auntie Fang.

233
00:21:33,125 --> 00:21:35,583
Kraeng. I have something to say.

234
00:21:37,291 --> 00:21:38,708
About your love for me...

235
00:21:39,708 --> 00:21:42,125
We are probably not meant for each other.

236
00:21:42,791 --> 00:21:44,708
You should forget all about me.

237
00:21:47,958 --> 00:21:50,583
You must live on without me.

238
00:21:50,958 --> 00:21:55,000
Don't be too sad after I'm gone.

239
00:21:56,416 --> 00:21:57,375
I'm going.

240
00:21:58,958 --> 00:21:59,958
I'm really going.

241
00:22:02,833 --> 00:22:04,250
I'm truly really going.

242
00:22:11,541 --> 00:22:13,125
Remember my face.

243
00:22:15,958 --> 00:22:20,375
Krai, what was Fang talking about?

244
00:22:22,375 --> 00:22:25,333
I have no idea. I think...

245
00:22:26,666 --> 00:22:28,083
she has a crush on you.

246
00:22:29,041 --> 00:22:31,875
No. No! No.

247
00:22:32,666 --> 00:22:34,625
Krai, tell me it's not true.

248
00:22:35,916 --> 00:22:37,125
No, no!

249
00:22:38,500 --> 00:22:42,833
Hey, Fang. We think it's time for us

250
00:22:43,125 --> 00:22:47,083
to volunteer to go spying
in Yasotharavadi. What do you think?

251
00:22:47,708 --> 00:22:49,916
I'm so worried about Kraeng.

252
00:22:52,333 --> 00:22:55,208
It's a critical time
and you're chucking down liquor.

253
00:22:55,291 --> 00:22:56,791
You think that's right?

254
00:22:58,500 --> 00:23:00,333
Gon is probably right.

255
00:23:00,583 --> 00:23:02,000
On one hand, I'm worried about Kraeng.

256
00:23:02,958 --> 00:23:04,750
On the other hand,
I'm worried about Kraeng.

257
00:23:07,500 --> 00:23:09,291
Why would you drink the liquor?

258
00:23:14,500 --> 00:23:18,375
Auntie Fang, if you don't go, I'll go.

259
00:23:18,791 --> 00:23:21,458
If you go, will you remember my face?

260
00:23:21,708 --> 00:23:24,208
-Of course.
-I wasn't talking about you.

261
00:23:25,166 --> 00:23:26,375
I meant Kraeng.

262
00:23:27,416 --> 00:23:31,041
But, Auntie Fang,
please don't punish yourself.

263
00:23:43,916 --> 00:23:46,750
Fang, I'll drink it for you.

264
00:23:48,250 --> 00:23:51,166
-Yeah. Help yourself.
-Of all the battles, none are as big

265
00:23:51,250 --> 00:23:54,250
as the war coming to our village.

266
00:23:54,458 --> 00:23:56,625
Nobody loves you more than me, Auntie.

267
00:23:56,708 --> 00:24:00,833
If you had good judgment,
you wouldn't be drinking like this.

268
00:24:01,416 --> 00:24:03,583
Why don't you love yourself?

269
00:24:04,750 --> 00:24:05,916
When we were young,

270
00:24:07,125 --> 00:24:09,250
I was your best friend, right?

271
00:24:10,291 --> 00:24:11,833
-Auntie Duen!
-No more for me.

272
00:24:11,916 --> 00:24:15,166
Where is our unity?

273
00:24:20,791 --> 00:24:27,333
So you guys are volunteering to spy
on Yasotharavadi with Horm, correct?

274
00:24:34,666 --> 00:24:36,375
We both will go as well.

275
00:24:37,833 --> 00:24:38,791
Yeah.

276
00:24:39,458 --> 00:24:41,083
Krai. Boontueng.

277
00:24:42,000 --> 00:24:43,375
That's good. So...

278
00:24:46,541 --> 00:24:47,375
Good.

279
00:24:48,333 --> 00:24:52,875
So our nation will overcome
the enemies and opponents.

280
00:24:53,250 --> 00:24:56,583
They are not enough.

281
00:24:57,833 --> 00:25:00,375
I'll go with them.

282
00:25:00,458 --> 00:25:01,833
-Auntie Fang!
-Fang!

283
00:25:02,041 --> 00:25:03,791
I knew you would come.

284
00:25:04,458 --> 00:25:06,250
I have thought it through.

285
00:25:06,750 --> 00:25:11,375
Between the nation and men,
I'd choose men.

286
00:25:12,083 --> 00:25:13,125
-Fang!
-Fang!

287
00:25:13,208 --> 00:25:15,416
I'm kidding.

288
00:25:15,666 --> 00:25:16,750
You guys.

289
00:25:17,875 --> 00:25:21,125
I could never leave my homeland
in jeopardy.

290
00:25:21,208 --> 00:25:24,750
I'm very good at prying
into someone's business. Believe me.

291
00:25:28,416 --> 00:25:29,916
Are you okay?

292
00:25:30,208 --> 00:25:31,875
You guzzled down all of my liquor.

293
00:25:32,125 --> 00:25:33,541
I didn't have any.

294
00:25:35,500 --> 00:25:36,500
It's so good

295
00:25:36,958 --> 00:25:39,500
that you guys are making a sacrifice
for our nation.

296
00:25:40,666 --> 00:25:42,250
I am relieved now.

297
00:25:42,541 --> 00:25:46,000
Those who have skills don't volunteer?

298
00:25:46,875 --> 00:25:49,000
If we let everyone go with you,

299
00:25:49,416 --> 00:25:52,083
then there will be no one to fight here.

300
00:25:52,250 --> 00:25:56,208
I have someone with skills
to teach you guys.

301
00:26:12,666 --> 00:26:17,250
This is the alchemist who will teach you
the magic spells.

302
00:26:18,041 --> 00:26:19,791
Learn them carefully

303
00:26:20,500 --> 00:26:24,875
-so you can use them in an emergency.
-Okay.

304
00:26:25,000 --> 00:26:29,625
I will teach you guys some spells
until you are good at it.

305
00:26:30,000 --> 00:26:36,458
Today, I'll teach you the spells to call
for wind, water, rain and everything.

306
00:26:37,041 --> 00:26:40,083
First, the water. Watch and learn.

307
00:26:51,041 --> 00:26:52,416
I was totally startled.

308
00:27:00,375 --> 00:27:01,791
-Fang.
-Yes?

309
00:27:02,041 --> 00:27:03,875
-It's your turn.
-To call for water?

310
00:27:04,125 --> 00:27:04,958
Yes.

311
00:27:17,708 --> 00:27:20,791
There. The water called by Fang.

312
00:27:23,666 --> 00:27:26,000
Fang, look!

313
00:27:26,500 --> 00:27:30,041
Is that the water you called or bubbles
from fish gobbling something?

314
00:27:30,125 --> 00:27:32,250
Yeah. Two bubbles are better than nothing.

315
00:27:32,916 --> 00:27:34,583
It's good enough for now.

316
00:27:35,083 --> 00:27:38,083
Keep practicing
and you'll get better, Fang.

317
00:27:38,166 --> 00:27:39,833
Yes, sir.

318
00:27:40,750 --> 00:27:43,458
Horm! Now it's your turn.

319
00:27:46,916 --> 00:27:48,000
Water.

320
00:27:52,166 --> 00:27:53,250
Water.

321
00:28:02,291 --> 00:28:04,458
Are you calling for more water,
Auntie Horm?

322
00:28:07,208 --> 00:28:10,250
Today, I'll teach you 15 poses
of Thai boxing.

323
00:28:15,083 --> 00:28:17,000
I'm lost from the beginning.

324
00:28:23,041 --> 00:28:24,000
So much screaming.

325
00:28:25,833 --> 00:28:27,125
What the heck?

326
00:28:27,916 --> 00:28:31,041
Are you guys really volunteering
to go to Yasotharavadi?

327
00:28:35,416 --> 00:28:38,541
Yuck! You guys overestimate yourselves,
don't you?

328
00:28:39,333 --> 00:28:42,916
Yeah. I bet you will not make it
back here.

329
00:28:56,541 --> 00:28:58,125
Is there a monkey show around here?

330
00:29:02,583 --> 00:29:06,000
No more. Luckily, I knew
he was going to do that.

331
00:29:07,375 --> 00:29:09,833
-Auntie Fang.
-What?

332
00:29:10,250 --> 00:29:11,958
Kraeng is here!

333
00:29:12,708 --> 00:29:15,291
Kraeng is here? See?

334
00:29:15,541 --> 00:29:18,416
I knew it! He surely has a crush on me.

335
00:29:19,458 --> 00:29:21,750
I think he's bringing elephants here
for a bath.

336
00:29:22,166 --> 00:29:24,291
Soi, don't lie to me. He came to see me.

337
00:29:24,375 --> 00:29:25,875
He really is, Auntie.

338
00:29:27,041 --> 00:29:28,250
Shit. I'm so embarrassed.

339
00:29:43,833 --> 00:29:46,000
No. It wasn't me.

340
00:30:05,875 --> 00:30:09,166
-Fang is so talented.
-Yeah.

341
00:30:09,250 --> 00:30:12,500
Men always compliment their wife.

342
00:30:21,791 --> 00:30:25,166
Don't be shy.

343
00:30:27,250 --> 00:30:29,458
Not you, Kraeng! It's you, Fang.

344
00:30:29,541 --> 00:30:30,583
Freaking Duen!

345
00:30:31,041 --> 00:30:32,041
Kraeng!

346
00:30:32,500 --> 00:30:33,541
Kraeng.

347
00:30:43,416 --> 00:30:46,875
I have blessed you guys
with warding spells.

348
00:30:48,000 --> 00:30:52,833
From now on, you all are invincible.

349
00:30:53,208 --> 00:30:55,291
You can't be physically harmed.

350
00:30:59,833 --> 00:31:02,375
Gon, step forward.

351
00:31:32,333 --> 00:31:33,916
Wait right here.

352
00:31:34,833 --> 00:31:37,208
I'll bring you the first aid kit.

353
00:31:44,291 --> 00:31:45,208
Where?

354
00:31:50,833 --> 00:31:52,000
Do you think she'll survive?

355
00:31:52,083 --> 00:31:54,000
She's all right. Don't you worry.

356
00:32:01,916 --> 00:32:03,583
Hey, Duen.

357
00:32:04,250 --> 00:32:06,750
-Yes, Dad?
-How are you doing?

358
00:32:12,000 --> 00:32:13,750
Dad. Mom.

359
00:32:14,541 --> 00:32:17,833
I have decided to go to Yasotharavadi.

360
00:32:18,458 --> 00:32:19,500
Duen.

361
00:32:21,708 --> 00:32:23,416
I didn't volunteer at first

362
00:32:24,333 --> 00:32:26,250
because I was worried about you both.

363
00:32:29,083 --> 00:32:30,708
Though I have a feminine mind...

364
00:32:33,875 --> 00:32:35,125
physically, I'm still a man.

365
00:32:35,875 --> 00:32:38,166
I have nothing to fear from the enemies.

366
00:32:40,958 --> 00:32:43,375
I am so proud of you.

367
00:32:45,083 --> 00:32:46,875
Though you're like this,

368
00:32:47,916 --> 00:32:52,833
I am confident
that you will accomplish this job.

369
00:32:54,291 --> 00:32:55,291
Yeah, Dad.

370
00:32:56,500 --> 00:33:00,875
Take care of yourself.
No need to worry about us.

371
00:33:01,833 --> 00:33:06,375
Your dad and I will pray to the gods

372
00:33:07,458 --> 00:33:09,250
to protect you

373
00:33:10,458 --> 00:33:14,083
until you come back.

374
00:33:25,541 --> 00:33:28,333
I have to leave home

375
00:33:28,416 --> 00:33:30,250
and you for a while.

376
00:33:33,541 --> 00:33:37,375
You're the only one
that I'm worried about.

377
00:33:44,083 --> 00:33:45,291
In this situation,

378
00:33:47,291 --> 00:33:51,041
I can't be thinking of just myself or you.

379
00:33:53,125 --> 00:33:56,541
Because if we can't accomplish this job,

380
00:33:58,458 --> 00:34:00,000
not only our lives

381
00:34:01,750 --> 00:34:03,916
but also everybody's lives here

382
00:34:04,875 --> 00:34:06,541
will come to an end.

383
00:34:10,500 --> 00:34:11,708
If I don't come back,

384
00:34:13,416 --> 00:34:15,291
promise me

385
00:34:16,208 --> 00:34:18,333
that you will take care of Kumlai for me.

386
00:34:20,166 --> 00:34:22,458
Can you do that, Chote?

387
00:34:25,875 --> 00:34:29,583
You have to promise me first
that you'll come back, my brother.

388
00:34:36,750 --> 00:34:37,666
Kumlai.

389
00:34:38,166 --> 00:34:40,500
Kumlai. Kumlai, I'm right here.

390
00:34:41,333 --> 00:34:42,750
You don't need to be afraid, Kumlai.

391
00:34:43,375 --> 00:34:44,583
Don't be afraid.

392
00:34:45,416 --> 00:34:46,916
No need to be afraid, Kumlai.

393
00:34:52,083 --> 00:34:53,208
I'm right here.

394
00:35:07,916 --> 00:35:09,375
Don't worry about me.

395
00:35:15,750 --> 00:35:17,416
If you really must go...

396
00:35:21,000 --> 00:35:22,458
I won't forbid you.

397
00:35:31,541 --> 00:35:33,875
Please show your grace to protect him.

398
00:36:04,041 --> 00:36:06,041
I will hurry and come back to you.

399
00:36:21,541 --> 00:36:24,791
Good luck, be safe, and be victorious.

400
00:36:27,791 --> 00:36:29,250
Amen.

401
00:36:32,000 --> 00:36:33,500
Rise!

402
00:36:45,458 --> 00:36:49,708
Find the monk Thammarong.

403
00:36:50,500 --> 00:36:52,666
He'll help you guys.

404
00:37:03,625 --> 00:37:06,541
Pick up the pace. Hurry.

405
00:37:08,416 --> 00:37:11,416
No more dillydallying.
It will be much harder after dark.

406
00:37:11,500 --> 00:37:15,541
Yeah. For big results, we need to be bold
and take risks.

407
00:37:16,250 --> 00:37:19,833
Next time, whatever happens,

408
00:37:20,166 --> 00:37:22,041
we have to follow it through.

409
00:37:22,500 --> 00:37:24,000
You're right, Duen.

410
00:37:26,208 --> 00:37:27,958
-Chote.
-Yeah?

411
00:37:28,666 --> 00:37:31,291
Please take good care of my mom and dad.

412
00:37:31,708 --> 00:37:33,083
Yes, I will.

413
00:37:35,291 --> 00:37:36,416
For the next meal,

414
00:37:37,541 --> 00:37:40,208
you've gotta find them some food.

415
00:37:40,458 --> 00:37:43,000
Duen. Are you saying your last words?

416
00:37:43,208 --> 00:37:45,125
Freaking Fang! I know,

417
00:37:45,833 --> 00:37:48,250
your dad is dead, your mom is dead.

418
00:37:48,708 --> 00:37:50,458
So you have no one to worry about.

419
00:37:50,958 --> 00:37:52,208
Yes, you're right.

420
00:37:53,750 --> 00:37:57,083
Your dad is dead, your mom is dead,
really?

421
00:38:00,750 --> 00:38:01,750
It's time to go.

422
00:38:03,083 --> 00:38:05,041
-Wait for me!
-Saeng.

423
00:38:05,125 --> 00:38:06,500
I'm here.

424
00:38:09,583 --> 00:38:11,708
Shouldn't you leave the liquor first,
Saeng?

425
00:38:11,791 --> 00:38:13,333
Be careful, Saeng.

426
00:38:13,541 --> 00:38:15,041
Wait for me.

427
00:38:52,000 --> 00:38:54,625
They are camping up that way.

428
00:38:55,125 --> 00:38:57,291
Walk for the time
it takes the rice to cook.

429
00:39:01,541 --> 00:39:04,958
Boontueng. You said the time
it takes the rice to cook.

430
00:39:05,291 --> 00:39:09,250
The rice would have been burnt by now.
When are we going to get there? Shit.

431
00:39:10,041 --> 00:39:12,666
Real soon. Be patient, Fang.

432
00:39:13,041 --> 00:39:16,083
Yeah, Fang. I agree with him.

433
00:39:16,250 --> 00:39:17,833
Be patient.

434
00:39:18,166 --> 00:39:21,000
Remember this. For big results,

435
00:39:21,083 --> 00:39:24,125
we need to be bold and take risks.
You don't agree?

436
00:39:24,208 --> 00:39:26,958
I am so hungry for it.

437
00:39:27,916 --> 00:39:29,791
Hungry for the fight, Auntie Duen?

438
00:39:30,125 --> 00:39:31,958
Food. I'm hungry for food, Soi.

439
00:39:32,375 --> 00:39:34,666
-Are you not?
-I am.

440
00:39:35,166 --> 00:39:38,125
I agree with Duen.
We have walked for a long time.

441
00:39:39,000 --> 00:39:42,375
No shower, no food at all.

442
00:39:42,750 --> 00:39:45,500
I am so hungry that I could die.

443
00:39:46,916 --> 00:39:50,833
You're right, Gon. Since I have known you,

444
00:39:51,041 --> 00:39:53,458
today is the only day
that you've said something right.

445
00:39:53,750 --> 00:39:56,250
You don't need to agree with me, Horm.

446
00:39:56,333 --> 00:39:58,250
So maybe we should stop and rest.

447
00:39:58,625 --> 00:40:03,833
And I'll find out early in the morning
where their camp is.

448
00:40:11,750 --> 00:40:14,500
Freaking Horm! Watch out!
You almost hit my face.

449
00:40:14,666 --> 00:40:16,083
So, move.

450
00:40:18,208 --> 00:40:19,416
Shit.

451
00:40:25,916 --> 00:40:30,083
Freaking Horm! I said that you almost hit
my face. What are you doing?

452
00:40:33,833 --> 00:40:34,958
Stop fighting.

453
00:40:35,833 --> 00:40:39,041
We should be united.
If we are fighting each other like this,

454
00:40:39,250 --> 00:40:41,333
how can we conquer any enemy?

455
00:40:41,750 --> 00:40:44,291
I think she's right.

456
00:40:44,708 --> 00:40:47,791
Whatever she says is right.

457
00:40:49,875 --> 00:40:51,000
Yeah?

458
00:40:54,125 --> 00:40:55,208
Could you stop doing that?

459
00:40:55,291 --> 00:40:57,250
So, walk away.

460
00:40:57,333 --> 00:40:59,083
Stop, stop!

461
00:41:00,041 --> 00:41:02,916
You didn't listen to what Fang just said?

462
00:41:03,916 --> 00:41:06,708
We need to be united.

463
00:41:07,000 --> 00:41:09,125
That's right, Duen.

464
00:41:09,208 --> 00:41:12,250
You guys went back to fighting
as soon as she'd said it.

465
00:41:14,708 --> 00:41:19,125
So, I think we should drink to make a vow
that we will be in harmony.

466
00:41:20,458 --> 00:41:21,750
I agree.

467
00:41:22,208 --> 00:41:26,500
To live and to die together. Be united.

468
00:41:26,583 --> 00:41:29,166
Okay. Let's drink to make a vow.

469
00:41:32,291 --> 00:41:34,125
Where is Saeng?

470
00:41:35,708 --> 00:41:36,708
Over there.

471
00:41:41,458 --> 00:41:43,041
-You freaking Saeng!
-Let's go.

472
00:41:43,750 --> 00:41:46,041
We can make a vow later
after he finishes peeing.

473
00:41:46,458 --> 00:41:47,625
I have drunk it.

474
00:41:47,708 --> 00:41:49,291
That's your problem. Let's go.

475
00:42:08,541 --> 00:42:13,916
I think their camp is not very far
beyond the cave ahead.

476
00:42:17,500 --> 00:42:18,458
This way. Hurry.

477
00:42:19,458 --> 00:42:20,666
Auntie Fang.

478
00:42:20,750 --> 00:42:22,125
What are you calling her for?

479
00:42:22,208 --> 00:42:23,875
Walk up to her.

480
00:42:35,291 --> 00:42:37,333
Krai. Where are they?

481
00:42:38,500 --> 00:42:40,833
Right there. On the bank of the river.

482
00:42:40,916 --> 00:42:42,333
Should we attack them now?

483
00:42:46,416 --> 00:42:47,291
Well...

484
00:42:47,958 --> 00:42:50,416
You didn't answer us, you just shot them.

485
00:42:50,791 --> 00:42:53,208
Duen, what are you gonna do?

486
00:42:53,416 --> 00:42:55,875
You guys, go!

487
00:43:27,166 --> 00:43:29,375
I dare you!

488
00:43:59,416 --> 00:44:00,291
You guys...

489
00:44:01,833 --> 00:44:04,500
they're all dead. We won!

490
00:44:04,583 --> 00:44:05,916
Hooray!

491
00:44:14,541 --> 00:44:18,041
I feel very disgusted dressing like them.

492
00:44:18,583 --> 00:44:22,125
You know that I despise them.

493
00:44:22,625 --> 00:44:24,041
You think I like this?

494
00:44:24,500 --> 00:44:26,583
Look. It hides all of my beauty.

495
00:44:27,625 --> 00:44:30,583
But I like it. There are lots of men here.

496
00:44:31,750 --> 00:44:36,000
Krai, for big results, we need to be bold
and take risks.

497
00:44:36,625 --> 00:44:38,416
We have to do whatever it takes.

498
00:44:40,458 --> 00:44:42,416
Walk straight. Don't show any red flags.

499
00:44:43,333 --> 00:44:44,541
What red flag?

500
00:44:45,833 --> 00:44:48,291
Fang. Gon.

501
00:44:49,041 --> 00:44:52,916
Do you know where they keep the liquor?

502
00:44:54,875 --> 00:44:59,666
Saeng! Can you not drink
at this moment? Jackass.

503
00:45:00,833 --> 00:45:05,916
Wow, Fang. If you were not this pretty,
I would have slapped your face.

504
00:45:06,458 --> 00:45:09,125
Don't believe him, Auntie Fang.
He's lying to you.

505
00:45:09,208 --> 00:45:11,208
He's not lying. It's probably true.

506
00:45:11,291 --> 00:45:12,541
Soi.

507
00:45:17,375 --> 00:45:18,791
What are you doing here?

508
00:45:18,875 --> 00:45:20,416
Right.

509
00:45:44,541 --> 00:45:45,875
That was a close call.

510
00:45:45,958 --> 00:45:48,458
Shit. Almost got ourselves discovered.

511
00:45:51,708 --> 00:45:55,333
Hurry and bring the woman you caught
to serve me here.

512
00:45:55,875 --> 00:45:56,833
Yes, sir.

513
00:45:58,208 --> 00:45:59,333
Krai, Krai.

514
00:45:59,416 --> 00:46:02,625
For big results, we need to be bold
and take risks.

515
00:46:02,708 --> 00:46:06,166
We have to do whatever it takes.

516
00:46:06,250 --> 00:46:08,916
You don't know any other words?

517
00:46:09,000 --> 00:46:10,416
I'm just reminding him.

518
00:46:11,791 --> 00:46:13,250
You'll surely see me fight.

519
00:46:14,000 --> 00:46:16,166
Krai. You're stepping on my foot.

520
00:46:18,375 --> 00:46:19,208
I'm sorry.

521
00:46:22,208 --> 00:46:24,333
Fang. Slow reaction?

522
00:46:24,458 --> 00:46:25,875
Yes, it is.

523
00:46:27,166 --> 00:46:28,333
I think it's bruised.

524
00:46:30,958 --> 00:46:33,500
Let go! Let go of me!

525
00:46:33,958 --> 00:46:36,541
