I am a monk.

782
01:11:31,791 --> 01:11:34,125
Yes, we see you as a monk.

783
01:11:35,125 --> 01:11:38,000
Or would you like us to see you
as something else.

784
01:11:38,083 --> 01:11:39,916
What would you like me to be?

785
01:11:40,791 --> 01:11:42,333
I'll be as such.

786
01:11:44,291 --> 01:11:48,083
What is he talking about? I'm so confused.

787
01:11:48,208 --> 01:11:51,166
Fang. Duen.

788
01:11:51,791 --> 01:11:54,166
Or is he the monk that we are looking for?

789
01:11:55,666 --> 01:11:57,000
I don't think so, Gon.

790
01:11:58,000 --> 01:12:00,625
I don't think he's the one
that is going to help us.

791
01:12:01,083 --> 01:12:02,291
Right, Fang?

792
01:12:03,833 --> 01:12:08,666
I am Thammarong. I'm the one
who is going to help you.

793
01:12:08,875 --> 01:12:11,166
See, Fang?

794
01:12:11,416 --> 01:12:15,375
I told you. And you don't believe me. See?

795
01:12:15,583 --> 01:12:18,125
Amen. We're so sorry.

796
01:12:19,166 --> 01:12:20,250
We would like to salute you.

797
01:12:20,833 --> 01:12:25,083
From now on, you have to call me
Ya Sin Visura.

798
01:12:26,500 --> 01:12:28,166
-Ya Sin...
-Visura.

799
01:12:29,041 --> 01:12:30,625
Who is that, Duen?

800
01:12:31,041 --> 01:12:32,333
How would I know?

801
01:12:32,958 --> 01:12:36,416
Me. That's my name in Yasotharavadi.

802
01:12:36,500 --> 01:12:38,875
-I see.
-I see.

803
01:12:39,250 --> 01:12:41,916
-Don't forget this name.
-Yes, sir.

804
01:12:43,416 --> 01:12:44,708
Be gentle.

805
01:12:46,791 --> 01:12:48,541
Do it gently.

806
01:12:52,625 --> 01:12:53,916
La Ong Inlay.

807
01:12:55,291 --> 01:12:57,708
The monk Ya Sin Visura is here.

808
01:13:12,666 --> 01:13:14,125
Namaste.

809
01:13:21,291 --> 01:13:25,416
You came to visit me here.
What can I do for you?

810
01:13:26,625 --> 01:13:31,500
My relatives came from Mawtamaeng.
Staying with me is inappropriate.

811
01:13:32,250 --> 01:13:36,333
So I'd like you to teach them
to do something

812
01:13:36,416 --> 01:13:38,250
in exchange for a place to sleep.

813
01:13:38,458 --> 01:13:40,125
Could you do that for me?

814
01:13:40,750 --> 01:13:45,833
Yes, sir. Since you know them,
I'll teach them.

815
01:13:46,875 --> 01:13:50,750
So that they can serve
the Royal family like us.

816
01:13:51,416 --> 01:13:54,166
Isn't that right, La Ong Inlay?

817
01:13:55,583 --> 01:13:57,958
I really appreciate it.

818
01:14:00,041 --> 01:14:03,416
And, you guys, work as hard as you can.

819
01:14:03,958 --> 01:14:05,000
-Yes, sir.
-Yes, sir.

820
01:14:07,000 --> 01:14:12,791
So Sew, follow me. I'll try to find a way
to get you into the army again.

821
01:14:13,041 --> 01:14:14,083
Yes, sir.

822
01:14:17,500 --> 01:14:20,125
You asked me to come here.
What can I do for you?

823
01:14:20,625 --> 01:14:23,458
I would like to ask you to enlist him
in the army

824
01:14:23,541 --> 01:14:28,666
under the command of your father,
Po Ong Tin. Can you help me?

825
01:14:30,500 --> 01:14:31,500
Him?

826
01:14:33,041 --> 01:14:34,708
Yes, sir. I'm Boon...

827
01:14:37,208 --> 01:14:38,833
My name is So Sew, sir.

828
01:14:40,500 --> 01:14:45,041
He's not from here, is he, sir?

829
01:14:48,125 --> 01:14:52,083
This man is just a commoner

830
01:14:52,958 --> 01:14:56,416
whose village was affected by the battle.
He came here,

831
01:14:57,208 --> 01:15:00,500
just hoping that his village will survive.

832
01:15:01,041 --> 01:15:05,208
He has nothing else to gain
from this battle.

833
01:15:07,291 --> 01:15:11,875
So I just hope that you could help him
to survive here

834
01:15:13,083 --> 01:15:15,666
until his job is done.

835
01:15:18,375 --> 01:15:21,250
Could you be of help to your mentor?

836
01:15:23,916 --> 01:15:27,083
Father, I don't agree with this battle.

837
01:15:27,375 --> 01:15:30,333
We have promised to end the war.

838
01:15:31,375 --> 01:15:35,166
So, why are we breaking our own word?

839
01:15:35,750 --> 01:15:38,125
We didn't want to end the war
from the beginning.

840
01:15:38,500 --> 01:15:42,375
We can't let Asoraya
be a worrisome loose end

841
01:15:42,666 --> 01:15:46,333
that could attack us at any time.

842
01:15:47,750 --> 01:15:50,958
You are my son. Just do what I say.

843
01:15:53,416 --> 01:15:56,000
I don't agree with everything in this war,

844
01:15:57,791 --> 01:16:00,333
and I'm grateful for your kindness.

845
01:16:02,333 --> 01:16:06,500
I'll take care of you and help
as seems appropriate.

846
01:16:07,625 --> 01:16:08,458
Thank you.

847
01:16:09,541 --> 01:16:11,375
Thank you very much.

848
01:16:16,500 --> 01:16:21,333
Master, since I'm about to take the army
to attack a city far from here,

849
01:16:22,375 --> 01:16:24,666
I would like to ask you for a talisman.

850
01:16:26,500 --> 01:16:28,000
Could you give me one?

851
01:16:28,625 --> 01:16:31,416
The thing you want

852
01:16:31,500 --> 01:16:35,458
is actually unnecessary.

853
01:16:36,416 --> 01:16:38,916
If you put your mind to it,

854
01:16:39,583 --> 01:16:44,375
you will succeed and win this battle.

855
01:16:45,541 --> 01:16:49,000
Please, Master. Give me a talisman

856
01:16:50,208 --> 01:16:52,333
to make me feel secure.

857
01:16:53,500 --> 01:16:56,625
If you really want it,

858
01:16:56,708 --> 01:17:02,291
I'll give you one.
I have kept it for over 20 years.

859
01:17:17,500 --> 01:17:21,750
-Ivory! You're so lucky.
-Ivory or a knife handle?

860
01:17:22,833 --> 01:17:26,833
Because of this, I've had to lie
on my stomach for 20 years.

861
01:17:27,541 --> 01:17:28,958
I'm giving it to you.

862
01:17:33,583 --> 01:17:34,750
Well, Master...

863
01:17:40,500 --> 01:17:42,000
Come on, help me here.

864
01:17:44,541 --> 01:17:45,583
Master...

865
01:17:49,708 --> 01:17:50,791
It hurts.

866
01:17:51,541 --> 01:17:52,750
It must have been in the bone.

867
01:17:53,500 --> 01:17:54,541
Master...

868
01:17:56,083 --> 01:17:58,000
Master, I think...

869
01:17:59,416 --> 01:18:03,375
that we should leave it like this.
Or you'll bleed to death.

870
01:18:04,750 --> 01:18:07,541
Yeah. Leave it where it is.

871
01:18:17,958 --> 01:18:20,250
Soi, be on the lookout for us.

872
01:18:21,041 --> 01:18:23,500
"Lookout", not look in, right?

873
01:18:25,875 --> 01:18:26,875
I'm going.

874
01:18:42,125 --> 01:18:45,083
Use the spell, Gon. Call him over.

875
01:19:01,000 --> 01:19:05,750
Come here.

876
01:19:07,208 --> 01:19:08,041
Stop.

877
01:19:10,250 --> 01:19:11,958
Where do you keep the battle plans?

878
01:19:12,541 --> 01:19:13,791
With me.

879
01:19:13,875 --> 01:19:15,375
Bring it to me right now.

880
01:19:29,583 --> 01:19:33,250
Your spell is no longer working. Let's go.

881
01:19:33,875 --> 01:19:35,000
Where?

882
01:19:35,666 --> 01:19:39,583
To wash our feet, of course.
They're soaked with pee.

883
01:19:41,666 --> 01:19:42,500
Damn it!

884
01:19:54,458 --> 01:19:55,583
-Fang.
-Yeah?

885
01:19:56,625 --> 01:20:01,583
We're standing here.
Aren't you afraid that they'll wake up?

886
01:20:02,833 --> 01:20:07,083
How could they?
Remember the sleeping spell?

887
01:20:07,416 --> 01:20:11,291
Just put them to sleep. And voila!

888
01:20:12,125 --> 01:20:15,375
I've never seen you being so smart
like you are today.

889
01:20:15,458 --> 01:20:16,708
Go ahead.

890
01:20:17,333 --> 01:20:21,541
I want to know
when they are taking the army there.

891
01:20:23,625 --> 01:20:25,166
Okay, you say the spell.

892
01:20:38,833 --> 01:20:40,291
What are you doing here?

893
01:20:44,000 --> 01:20:47,708
Buatong and Tongkayee asked me to see
if you are asleep.

894
01:20:47,791 --> 01:20:49,458
Isn't that right?

895
01:20:50,125 --> 01:20:52,041
Fang, Fang.

896
01:20:55,208 --> 01:20:56,583
Oh, my God, you two.

897
01:20:57,833 --> 01:21:00,083
Sleeping like a log. How am I gonna move?

898
01:21:06,041 --> 01:21:09,625
How's it going, you two? No more bragging?

899
01:21:10,083 --> 01:21:12,875
-You also failed last night, didn't you?
-What?

900
01:21:13,083 --> 01:21:16,916
-What about you two?
-Yeah, you shouldn't say anything mean.

901
01:21:17,000 --> 01:21:18,208
Stop fighting for a little bit.

902
01:21:18,916 --> 01:21:21,958
Fang, what are we gonna do now?

903
01:21:22,666 --> 01:21:26,416
We've been here for quite some time.
We still haven't got any information.

904
01:21:26,500 --> 01:21:29,708
I've been busy with your quarrel,
so I haven't had time to think.

905
01:21:30,083 --> 01:21:33,958
Think about what? Your plans always fail.

906
01:21:37,041 --> 01:21:39,250
The witch doctor.

907
01:21:39,333 --> 01:21:40,833
Which doctor?

908
01:21:41,708 --> 01:21:43,583
The alchemist gave us some good stuff.

909
01:21:44,458 --> 01:21:45,791
What good stuff, Fang?

910
01:21:45,875 --> 01:21:47,416
What's the good stuff?

911
01:21:47,500 --> 01:21:49,791
I totally forgot. Shit.

912
01:21:50,000 --> 01:21:51,875
-Bitch. Took this long to remember.
-Here.

913
01:21:51,958 --> 01:21:53,500
Here. Hold this.

914
01:21:53,708 --> 01:21:55,875
It's a sedative.

915
01:21:55,958 --> 01:21:56,791
-What?
-What?

916
01:21:56,875 --> 01:21:58,333
Pour it here, Duen.

917
01:21:59,125 --> 01:22:02,083
Whoever inhales it,

918
01:22:02,833 --> 01:22:04,375
in the blink of an eye...

919
01:22:08,166 --> 01:22:09,125
Auntie Fang!

920
01:22:10,666 --> 01:22:13,458
Fang, Fang. What's wrong with Fang?

921
01:22:14,416 --> 01:22:17,083
Fang, Fang.

922
01:22:17,166 --> 01:22:18,083
It's very potent.

923
01:22:18,291 --> 01:22:20,291
It's almost time to go to the battle.

924
01:22:21,541 --> 01:22:24,291
Is everything ready?

925
01:22:26,250 --> 01:22:27,583
Yes, sir.

926
01:22:28,958 --> 01:22:32,166
I think we will win this battle.

927
01:22:32,833 --> 01:22:37,583
The weapons and artillery are ready to go.
You don't need to worry.

928
01:22:39,458 --> 01:22:44,625
Don't let anyone in Asoraya know
about this plan.

929
01:22:45,416 --> 01:22:51,000
If anyone gets in our way, kill them.

930
01:22:51,166 --> 01:22:54,416
I won't lose this battle.

931
01:23:14,791 --> 01:23:16,708
Take good care of yourself, Dad.

932
01:23:17,833 --> 01:23:18,666
I'm leaving now.

933
01:23:35,416 --> 01:23:36,500
Where are you going?

934
01:23:36,875 --> 01:23:39,000
I'm going to the room for dancing girls.

935
01:23:51,625 --> 01:23:53,500
-Are you a dancer?
-Yes, sir.

936
01:24:14,833 --> 01:24:17,583
How was it, Horm? Did you succeed?

937
01:24:21,708 --> 01:24:24,250
Horm!

938
01:24:26,083 --> 01:24:31,083
Horm! Horm, Horm, Horm.

939
01:24:33,041 --> 01:24:34,541
Just like me.

940
01:24:51,000 --> 01:24:52,666
Mue Tor. Tor Pa Yee.

941
01:24:53,000 --> 01:24:56,166
Go tell La Ong Inlay

942
01:24:56,291 --> 01:25:00,333
that I thank her for training the girls
to dance so gracefully.

943
01:25:00,958 --> 01:25:01,916
-I will.
-I will.

944
01:25:20,375 --> 01:25:24,000
Who are these girls?

945
01:25:24,291 --> 01:25:27,958
They are relatives of the monk
Ya Sin Visura.

946
01:25:28,291 --> 01:25:33,625
He asked La Ong Inlay and us to teach them
how to serve the Royal family.

947
01:25:34,750 --> 01:25:41,666
So we both think that they should serve
the Prince and My Ladies.

948
01:25:44,791 --> 01:25:45,791
Great.

949
01:25:47,541 --> 01:25:51,250
You two shall give them proper training.

950
01:25:52,625 --> 01:25:54,625
Let me see your faces.

951
01:25:55,125 --> 01:25:59,958
All of you, please look up
to let the Prince see your faces.

952
01:26:05,083 --> 01:26:06,458
Have them beheaded!

953
01:26:06,625 --> 01:26:08,541
My Lord, calm down.

954
01:26:08,625 --> 01:26:10,083
Wait, My Lord.

955
01:26:11,916 --> 01:26:12,958
Get them out of here.

956
01:26:16,500 --> 01:26:18,958
Hurry up. Get out of here.

957
01:26:19,041 --> 01:26:20,708
You two as well.

958
01:26:23,250 --> 01:26:24,083
Wait.

959
01:26:26,208 --> 01:26:27,291
Not you two.

960
01:26:30,333 --> 01:26:31,500
Them.

961
01:26:33,291 --> 01:26:35,208
Get out.

962
01:26:35,291 --> 01:26:37,541
-Yes, Your Highness.
-Yes, Your Highness.

963
01:26:46,416 --> 01:26:47,583
Such useless staff.

964
01:26:48,500 --> 01:26:52,833
How is it going with the auspicious time
for the army?

965
01:26:52,916 --> 01:26:54,833
-Yes, Your Majesty.
-Yes, Your Majesty.

966
01:26:54,916 --> 01:26:57,458
For the most auspicious time

967
01:26:57,541 --> 01:27:04,041
to take the army into battle,
the Prince should leave Yasotharavadi

968
01:27:04,125 --> 01:27:06,541
from dawn to dusk

969
01:27:06,750 --> 01:27:09,958
on the 12th waxing moon day
in the first lunar month.

970
01:27:10,166 --> 01:27:12,041
I don't agree.

971
01:27:12,750 --> 01:27:18,291
The most auspicious time
is not the one the priest Mayatai said.

972
01:27:19,041 --> 01:27:23,750
Rather, it is from dusk to dawn,

973
01:27:24,000 --> 01:27:27,291
on the 12th waning moon day
in the second lunar month.

974
01:27:27,708 --> 01:27:31,666
That is the most auspicious time
for the Prince

975
01:27:31,750 --> 01:27:34,291
to take the army.

976
01:27:35,291 --> 01:27:36,875
So which one is it?

977
01:27:38,666 --> 01:27:40,500
Priest Pawatin,

978
01:27:40,875 --> 01:27:44,250
I'm sure your time is best for my son.

979
01:27:45,041 --> 01:27:48,833
I don't think so.
The priest Mayatai's time

980
01:27:48,916 --> 01:27:51,833
should be best for the Prince.

981
01:27:52,083 --> 01:27:57,541
I'm afraid that if you go
at the priest Pawatin's time,

982
01:27:58,208 --> 01:28:00,458
you won't be victorious.

983
01:28:00,833 --> 01:28:02,291
Enough!

984
01:28:04,208 --> 01:28:07,208
You two'd better talk
and come to a conclusion.

985
01:28:07,833 --> 01:28:09,583
Then let me know.

986
01:28:10,583 --> 01:28:12,583
Don't fight in front of me like this.

987
01:28:14,041 --> 01:28:18,291
I don't need to listen to your argument.

988
01:28:21,083 --> 01:28:23,250
If there is no conclusion
by the next meeting,

989
01:28:24,208 --> 01:28:27,041
I'll have you all beheaded.

990
01:28:58,833 --> 01:29:00,833
You've got all the information, right?

991
01:29:01,208 --> 01:29:04,666
I heard that they'll move the army
in the first and second lunar months.

992
01:29:05,000 --> 01:29:08,250
At dawn and at dusk.
Did you hear the same?

993
01:29:08,333 --> 01:29:10,666
How are they gonna do that?
Both in the first and second lunar months?

994
01:29:10,750 --> 01:29:14,000
Neither of those times.
They all are going to get beheaded.

995
01:29:14,833 --> 01:29:15,875
Me?

996
01:29:16,416 --> 01:29:21,125
Damn. Not you. And not us.

997
01:29:21,583 --> 01:29:25,875
But the two priests. If they can't find
the most auspicious time.

998
01:29:26,875 --> 01:29:30,875
What are we gonna do now?
When can we go back home, then?

999
01:29:30,958 --> 01:29:35,125
I think next time we should get closer
to hear it more clearly.

1000
01:29:35,208 --> 01:29:39,958
Yeah, Fang. If you want to hear it
more clearly next time,

1001
01:29:40,041 --> 01:29:43,333
you would have to piggyback on the Prince.

1002
01:29:43,541 --> 01:29:45,541
Would he let her do that?

1003
01:29:48,000 --> 01:29:50,041
Found the battle plan?
It must be here somewhere.

1004
01:29:50,125 --> 01:29:53,333
You two hurry up before someone comes in.

1005
01:29:53,416 --> 01:29:54,875
Fang, I've found nothing.

1006
01:30:01,583 --> 01:30:04,875
Oh, God, someone is coming.
Fang, Fang, run!

1007
01:30:20,791 --> 01:30:24,166
-Nothing in there.
-Wonder where they put it.

1008
01:30:25,583 --> 01:30:26,750
Somebody's coming.

1009
01:30:41,458 --> 01:30:43,041
Hurry up, Auntie.

1010
01:30:43,125 --> 01:30:45,458
What about Gon and Horm?
Won't they be caught?

1011
01:30:46,458 --> 01:30:48,250
-Soi.
-Duen, Duen.

1012
01:30:48,333 --> 01:30:50,375
This way. Soi.

1013
01:30:52,000 --> 01:30:54,000
They're right behind us.

1014
01:30:55,750 --> 01:30:57,750
What should we do? They found us.

1015
01:30:57,833 --> 01:31:00,083
What can we do but run?

1016
01:31:02,958 --> 01:31:04,250
They're coming.

1017
01:31:59,666 --> 01:32:00,875
Fang.

1018
01:32:01,041 --> 01:32:02,416
What should we do now?

1019
01:32:02,500 --> 01:32:04,041
Whatever it is, let's do it.

1020
01:32:04,625 --> 01:32:06,541
I know what we should do.

1021
01:32:08,875 --> 01:32:12,416
On the 11th of the waxing moon, at dawn,

1022
01:32:12,500 --> 01:32:16,000
at 7:00 a.m. of the second lunar month,

1023
01:32:16,083 --> 01:32:19,541
which is the auspicious time for victory,
so suitable for the Prince

1024
01:32:19,625 --> 01:32:21,958
to move the army.

1025
01:32:25,083 --> 01:32:26,333
Mung Tra Bureng,

1026
01:32:27,041 --> 01:32:30,208
have you got your army ready?

1027
01:32:31,291 --> 01:32:35,458
For the auspicious time that the priest
just said, I have the army ready

1028
01:32:35,541 --> 01:32:37,750
for the battle, Father.

1029
01:32:39,083 --> 01:32:40,000
Great.

1030
01:32:40,291 --> 01:32:42,791
To celebrate this auspicious time,

1031
01:32:43,375 --> 01:32:45,041
I have prepared dancers

1032
01:32:45,541 --> 01:32:49,375
to dance in front of His Majesty
and my son

1033
01:32:50,291 --> 01:32:52,333
as entertainment before the war.

1034
01:33:20,083 --> 01:33:22,166
Which dancer do you like?

1035
01:33:23,291 --> 01:33:25,166
I'll bring her to you.

1036
01:33:44,125 --> 01:33:45,583
Commander Po Ong Tin...

1037
01:33:56,041 --> 01:33:57,291
Your Highness...

1038
01:33:59,833 --> 01:34:02,583
these dancers could be spies.

1039
01:34:02,666 --> 01:34:05,000
Duen, we didn't practice this pose.

1040
01:34:16,041 --> 01:34:18,416
Stop! Soldiers!

1041
01:34:18,958 --> 01:34:21,500
Take these dancers to the prison.

1042
01:34:37,375 --> 01:34:38,333
Auntie Fang!

1043
01:34:48,666 --> 01:34:52,375
These dancers could be spies

1044
01:34:52,458 --> 01:34:55,041
infiltrating us to get information
about the battle.

1045
01:35:23,083 --> 01:35:24,791
Let go of me. Let go now!

1046
01:35:25,416 --> 01:35:27,000
Duen.

1047
01:35:27,666 --> 01:35:30,125
I can walk in there myself.

1048
01:35:41,125 --> 01:35:43,625
You guys, what happened?

1049
01:35:43,708 --> 01:35:47,000
Duen, you tell him.
It's because of you, isn't it?

1050
01:35:48,375 --> 01:35:50,541
You always blame me.

1051
01:35:50,666 --> 01:35:52,916
If you guys could dance delicately
like me,

1052
01:35:53,000 --> 01:35:54,791
we wouldn't have been caught.

1053
01:35:55,125 --> 01:35:58,583
Geez. You danced like a monkey.

1054
01:35:59,000 --> 01:36:01,041
Yeah. Anybody could see through that.

1055
01:36:01,125 --> 01:36:02,500
-Yeah.
-Enough.

1056
01:36:02,750 --> 01:36:07,416
Stop fighting. We'd better figure out
how to get out of here.

1057
01:36:07,500 --> 01:36:09,000
How are we gonna get out of here?

1058
01:36:09,083 --> 01:36:11,125
What are we gonna do now?

1059
01:36:12,708 --> 01:36:14,333
I don't know, either.

1060
01:36:25,875 --> 01:36:29,875
Tomorrow is the most auspicious time

1061
01:36:29,958 --> 01:36:34,541
for me to take the army into battle.
So I came here to say goodbye.

1062
01:36:36,875 --> 01:36:42,583
-Tomorrow?
-But I still lack confidence,

1063
01:36:42,666 --> 01:36:49,291
as I'm worried that this battle
is not like anything in the past.

1064
01:36:50,250 --> 01:36:51,666
Actually,

1065
01:36:53,125 --> 01:36:55,833
the auspicious time is not
what matters the most.

1066
01:36:57,000 --> 01:37:01,625
Be confident, be brave.

1067
01:37:02,333 --> 01:37:07,041
And you'll win
no matter what the auspicious time is.

1068
01:37:10,666 --> 01:37:14,250
Your advice is very helpful.

1069
01:37:15,041 --> 01:37:19,000
I'll keep that in mind
and follow it through.

1070
01:37:21,250 --> 01:37:22,875
Bless you.

1071
01:37:23,750 --> 01:37:29,625
Be safe and sound. Return victorious.

1072
01:37:37,541 --> 01:37:38,958
Your Highness...

1073
01:37:42,375 --> 01:37:44,625
if you're still worried...

1074
01:37:57,958 --> 01:38:00,583
then take this.

1075
01:38:07,208 --> 01:38:09,083
This is just the handle.
Where is the rest?

1076
01:38:12,791 --> 01:38:14,791
Come to get the blade next time.

1077
01:38:19,000 --> 01:38:20,875
Stop the bleeding.

1078
01:38:23,000 --> 01:38:24,041
It's all right.

1079
01:38:24,125 --> 01:38:26,250
Take care of him. I must go now.

1080
01:38:27,583 --> 01:38:29,291
Be safe and sound.

1081
01:38:31,875 --> 01:38:33,250
-Master!
-Master!

1082
01:38:33,666 --> 01:38:35,458
Master, master!

1083
01:38:50,000 --> 01:38:56,625
Saeng, Boontueng, and Soi...
I wonder how they are doing.

1084
01:38:58,083 --> 01:39:02,541
They are moving the army tomorrow.
What are we gonna do?

1085
01:39:07,000 --> 01:39:09,333
If we can't get out of here,

1086
01:39:10,291 --> 01:39:13,458
everything we have done will be in vain.

1087
01:39:16,875 --> 01:39:20,625
The villagers alone can't fight them off.

1088
01:39:23,000 --> 01:39:24,208
I'm so worried.

1089
01:39:24,750 --> 01:39:27,166
If the village is ruined because of me...

1090
01:39:29,125 --> 01:39:30,541
I would rather die.

1091
01:39:31,750 --> 01:39:33,625
Don't say that, Duen.

1092
01:39:34,708 --> 01:39:36,125
If we must die...

1093
01:39:37,791 --> 01:39:39,708
we all should die together.

1094
01:39:41,458 --> 01:39:44,333
-Fang!
-I'm serious.

1095
01:39:48,958 --> 01:39:53,250
Darling, look at the moon. It's so pretty.

1096
01:39:53,791 --> 01:39:58,083
Please, all angels,

1097
01:39:58,375 --> 01:40:03,791
please protect my son Duen from any harm.

1098
01:40:04,958 --> 01:40:08,000
-Please.
-Please protect my son.

1099
01:40:24,208 --> 01:40:25,750
Saeng, my son.

1100
01:40:27,958 --> 01:40:30,416
I wonder how you are doing.

1101
01:40:53,625 --> 01:40:56,791
I, as the King

1102
01:40:56,875 --> 01:41:03,708
and your father, would like to give you
blessings to win this battle.

1103
01:41:05,458 --> 01:41:07,375
Thank you, Father.

1104
01:41:12,333 --> 01:41:16,416
I will bring you the victory
without doubt.

1105
01:41:17,125 --> 01:41:19,458
Bring me the victory.

1106
01:41:39,375 --> 01:41:43,875
You two hurry up and go help the others
before it's too late.

1107
01:41:47,750 --> 01:41:49,541
Saeng!

1108
01:41:50,500 --> 01:41:51,916
How are you doing, Boontueng?

1109
01:41:52,916 --> 01:41:55,250
It's time to do it.

1110
01:41:56,166 --> 01:41:58,583
We'll go help Krai and the rest.

1111
01:41:59,291 --> 01:42:01,916
You should get everything ready.

1112
01:42:02,833 --> 01:42:06,083
Don't worry. I'll do it.

1113
01:42:14,583 --> 01:42:16,166
Thongdee. Chote.

1114
01:42:17,375 --> 01:42:18,666
What's the matter, Puek?

1115
01:42:18,750 --> 01:42:20,458
Boontueng has sent a message.

1116
01:42:29,833 --> 01:42:31,500
-Hurry up, Soi.
-Auntie Fang.

1117
01:42:35,666 --> 01:42:37,000
-Soi.
-I'm here to help.

1118
01:42:37,083 --> 01:42:38,375
-Soi.
-Krai.

1119
01:42:38,458 --> 01:42:39,833
Come on.

1120
01:42:39,916 --> 01:42:41,916
-Go.
-Hurry before they all come.

1121
01:42:42,750 --> 01:42:44,000
Hurry up.

1122
01:42:50,000 --> 01:42:53,291
Hurry, come on.

1123
01:42:59,666 --> 01:43:02,958
Saeng, why are you sitting there?

1124
01:43:03,208 --> 01:43:04,541
I'm waiting for you guys.

1125
01:43:08,458 --> 01:43:10,583
Guys,

1126
01:43:10,666 --> 01:43:11,666
where is Gon?

1127
01:43:12,583 --> 01:43:13,708
-Yeah. Gon.
-I'm here.

1128
01:43:13,791 --> 01:43:15,583
Gon, hurry up.

1129
01:43:15,666 --> 01:43:17,416
Don't drag your feet.

1130
01:43:17,791 --> 01:43:22,833
Hurry. I have all the weapons,
clothes, and horses ready over there.

1131
01:43:23,291 --> 01:43:24,333
-Let's go.
-Hold on.

1132
01:43:25,208 --> 01:43:26,333
I have an idea.

1133
01:43:27,625 --> 01:43:28,958
Doksok.

1134
01:43:30,666 --> 01:43:35,000
You and I have been friends
for a long time.

1135
01:43:36,458 --> 01:43:37,625
I think it's time...

1136
01:43:39,458 --> 01:43:44,500
that we all cut ourselves
to make a vow to be friends forever.

1137
01:43:44,583 --> 01:43:45,500
Good.

1138
01:43:47,166 --> 01:43:48,333
Let heaven and earth be the witness.

1139
01:43:48,416 --> 01:43:50,958
Seventeen layers of heaven,
15 layers of earth,

1140
01:43:51,041 --> 01:43:53,500
forest, and mountain angels,
please be the witness.

1141
01:43:53,583 --> 01:43:58,250
If I or any of you guys face a threat,
I will totally fight by your side.

1142
01:43:58,333 --> 01:44:00,666
But if I face a threat, you all will--

1143
01:44:00,750 --> 01:44:02,625
-Duen!
-I'm not done.

1144
01:44:02,708 --> 01:44:04,875
I'm bleeding to death!

1145
01:44:05,625 --> 01:44:06,666
-Give me the knife.
-Here.

1146
01:44:12,875 --> 01:44:14,666
Doksok,

1147
01:44:15,666 --> 01:44:16,958
I have cut myself.

1148
01:44:28,625 --> 01:44:30,916
I'll send a message to my forever friends.

1149
01:44:31,000 --> 01:44:32,541
So they come to help us.

1150
01:44:32,625 --> 01:44:35,458
Shit. Where are you gonna find a pigeon
right now?

1151
01:44:35,750 --> 01:44:36,750
I have one right here.

1152
01:44:46,333 --> 01:44:48,333
Gon, we're leaving now.

1153
01:44:48,416 --> 01:44:49,833
Wait for me!

1154
01:44:49,916 --> 01:44:55,000
Thank you very much, Pi Day Gong.
With fate, we shall see each other again.

1155
01:44:58,458 --> 01:45:02,000
So, Kraeng, Klar, Kriang,

1156
01:45:02,291 --> 01:45:06,125
go tell everybody to get ready.

1157
01:45:06,208 --> 01:45:07,208
Yes, sir.

1158
01:45:10,375 --> 01:45:12,500
-All of you as well.
-Yes, sir.

1159
01:45:22,083 --> 01:45:24,666
Saeng, don't let them go
through the village.

1160
01:45:24,958 --> 01:45:26,500
You can count on me, Boontueng.

1161
01:45:27,833 --> 01:45:29,791
They have to face someone like me.

1162
01:45:30,166 --> 01:45:34,291
For my nation,
I will never let them go through.

1163
01:45:34,875 --> 01:45:38,750
I'll let them know that the people
of Kung Raga

1164
01:45:39,208 --> 01:45:42,500
are not afraid to fight to the death.
Let's go.

1165
01:45:44,750 --> 01:45:46,541
Go.

1166
01:45:46,625 --> 01:45:48,458
Go.

1167
01:45:49,041 --> 01:45:50,375
Go.

1168
01:45:50,708 --> 01:45:52,875
Hurry up, everyone, before it's too late.

1169
01:45:55,625 --> 01:46:00,416
Horm. Fang. Duen. Hold on! Wait for me!

1170
01:46:11,500 --> 01:46:13,916
Let all the good deeds I have done
be the power

1171
01:46:14,583 --> 01:46:19,125
to protect everyone of Kung Raga

1172
01:46:19,833 --> 01:46:24,125
and help them to survive any threats
in this battle.

1173
01:46:31,666 --> 01:46:33,000
-Sher!
-What?

1174
01:46:33,083 --> 01:46:34,500
Something terrible is happening!

1175
01:46:34,583 --> 01:46:37,416
Oh, Fai. What's wrong?

1176
01:46:37,500 --> 01:46:39,666
The chief is calling everyone
to fight a battle.

1177
01:46:39,791 --> 01:46:40,625
A battle?

1178
01:46:40,708 --> 01:46:42,416
Sher. Shor.

1179
01:46:42,500 --> 01:46:43,791
What?

1180
01:46:44,333 --> 01:46:47,208
Sher, no need to go.

1181
01:46:47,291 --> 01:46:49,000
Why do we need to fight?

1182
01:46:49,250 --> 01:46:52,500
We could just move
and escape from the enemy.

1183
01:46:53,125 --> 01:46:56,291
Because of people like you two,

1184
01:46:56,375 --> 01:46:58,375
our nation has been endlessly
losing our land.

1185
01:46:59,583 --> 01:47:01,666
It's just land. You don't need to care.

1186
01:47:01,750 --> 01:47:04,500
You are so old.
If you go, I'm sure you'll die.

1187
01:47:05,250 --> 01:47:08,208
Bitches! No matter how old or young,
we have to fight

1188
01:47:08,291 --> 01:47:10,333
for our Kung Raga village.

1189
01:47:13,500 --> 01:47:16,208
I will fight with them.

1190
01:47:17,416 --> 01:47:21,250
I despise them.
You two, go get weapons ready.

1191
01:47:23,208 --> 01:47:25,791
Meet at the front of the village
in a moment.

1192
01:47:39,000 --> 01:47:41,291
Master!

1193
01:47:42,541 --> 01:47:45,583
Master!

1194
01:47:46,000 --> 01:47:48,625
Master!

1195
01:47:57,541 --> 01:48:01,250
The enemy is coming toward us.
What should we do?

1196
01:48:01,750 --> 01:48:06,541
If that is so, this battle is inevitable.

1197
01:48:06,625 --> 01:48:10,791
Fight for our nation! Fear no one!

1198
01:48:15,208 --> 01:48:19,791
If we do not fight today, we won't have
a nation for our descendants.

1199
01:48:20,083 --> 01:48:23,250
Fight for our nation!

1200
01:48:23,458 --> 01:48:25,958
Fight for our nation!

1201
01:48:26,416 --> 01:48:28,958
Fight for our nation!

1202
01:48:29,041 --> 01:48:31,625
Fight for our nation!

1203
01:48:31,708 --> 01:48:34,000
Fight for our nation!

1204
01:48:34,083 --> 01:48:36,208
Fight for our nation!

1205
01:50:02,500 --> 01:50:03,541
Are you okay?

1206
01:51:21,208 --> 01:51:24,708
The master's talisman is really powerful.

1207
01:51:43,625 --> 01:51:45,833
-Let's go.
-Yeah.

1208
01:52:37,000 --> 01:52:38,458
Doctor!

1209
01:52:39,416 --> 01:52:40,333
Witch doctor!

1210
01:52:40,500 --> 01:52:43,958
Horm. I don't think I can make it.

1211
01:52:44,166 --> 01:52:47,500
What? No! You'll be all right.

1212
01:52:47,625 --> 01:52:50,500
No! You gotta be all right.

1213
01:52:56,291 --> 01:52:58,666
Not me. I didn't do it.

1214
01:52:59,458 --> 01:53:00,500
I didn't do it.

1215
01:53:17,041 --> 01:53:20,208
Kraeng. My dear Kraeng.

1216
01:53:25,708 --> 01:53:28,208
Kraeng, are you all right?

1217
01:53:30,500 --> 01:53:33,958
Leave him alone!
You have to go through me.

1218
01:53:42,958 --> 01:53:44,666
-Yes!
-Gon.

1219
01:53:44,750 --> 01:53:47,625
I have something to tell you. Gon!

1220
01:53:47,708 --> 01:53:50,958
Stop calling my name.
Hand me a cannon ball now!

1221
01:53:52,583 --> 01:53:55,166
-Which one? This?
-Yeah.

1222
01:53:58,541 --> 01:53:59,375
Move aside.

1223
01:54:26,000 --> 01:54:30,083
Daorueng!

1224
01:54:34,291 --> 01:54:36,291
There are no more.

1225
01:54:36,541 --> 01:54:38,375
No more? So we leave!

1226
01:55:02,666 --> 01:55:03,500
Kumlai!

1227
01:55:13,875 --> 01:55:14,708
Kumlai.

1228
01:55:20,083 --> 01:55:21,541
How are you holding up?

1229
01:55:24,083 --> 01:55:25,000
Kumlai.

1230
01:55:30,833 --> 01:55:32,041
Kumlai.

1231
01:55:45,583 --> 01:55:46,708
Daorueng!

1232
01:55:47,916 --> 01:55:49,916
No! Our baby!

1233
01:55:53,875 --> 01:55:54,833
You!

1234
01:57:02,458 --> 01:57:03,416
Mom!

1235
01:57:10,041 --> 01:57:10,958
Mom.

1236
01:57:13,833 --> 01:57:16,000
-Saeng.
-Mom.

1237
01:57:16,291 --> 01:57:17,750
Saeng, my baby.

1238
01:57:19,000 --> 01:57:21,416
You don't need to say anything.

1239
01:57:23,916 --> 01:57:29,500
I'm so glad to see you hold a sword
and fight.

1240
01:57:38,958 --> 01:57:40,708
Mom!

1241
01:57:47,250 --> 01:57:48,083
Mom!

1242
01:57:50,208 --> 01:57:51,041
Mom.

1243
01:57:52,208 --> 01:57:53,250
Duen.

1244
01:57:54,625 --> 01:57:57,458
No dad, no mom...

1245
01:57:58,500 --> 01:58:00,583
Take care of yourself, okay?

1246
01:58:01,000 --> 01:58:02,500
No, Mom.

1247
01:58:03,375 --> 01:58:07,000
It can't be like this. Mom. Mom!

1248
01:58:07,791 --> 01:58:11,750
I can rest in peace now, my baby.

1249
01:58:15,500 --> 01:58:21,500
Don't cry. You are a man.
You have to defend our nation.

1250
01:58:22,833 --> 01:58:25,500
Hold a sword to fight...

1251
01:58:27,791 --> 01:58:31,166
for our descendants.

1252
01:58:32,125 --> 01:58:33,208
Mom!

1253
01:58:38,375 --> 01:58:42,291
Mom!

1254
01:58:45,250 --> 01:58:48,208
No!

1255
01:58:51,125 --> 01:58:53,208
Mom!

1256
01:59:38,125 --> 01:59:42,125
You mean, we couldn't defend our city
and men?

1257
01:59:42,583 --> 01:59:43,750
Yes, Your Majesty.

1258
01:59:45,666 --> 01:59:49,833
If our city had great leaders,

1259
01:59:50,916 --> 01:59:53,916
not those noblemen,

1260
01:59:54,000 --> 01:59:58,541
who are treacherous, ignorant cowards

1261
01:59:58,625 --> 02:00:02,625
that let the enemy in to ruin our nation.

1262
02:00:03,833 --> 02:00:08,666
It doesn't matter if we had ten times
more people and soldiers than the enemy,

1263
02:00:09,500 --> 02:00:12,708
we couldn't have won this battle.

1264
02:00:13,500 --> 02:00:19,291
That's because we are divided, isn't it?

1265
02:00:33,333 --> 02:00:34,500
You die!

1266
02:01:36,333 --> 02:01:41,083
Duen! We are here for you.

1267
02:01:42,000 --> 02:01:47,875
Doksok, Doksok. Oh, God, you came
to help me. I'll survive!

1268
02:02:18,833 --> 02:02:20,208
Duen!

1269
02:03:12,625 --> 02:03:18,625
Not long after that, in 2112 B.C.E.,

1270
02:03:18,875 --> 02:03:24,250
Yasotharavadi returned to attack Asoraya
once more

1271
02:03:24,750 --> 02:03:30,833
because Asoraya was still divided and weak

1272
02:03:30,916 --> 02:03:33,166
from the previous battle.

1273
02:03:33,250 --> 02:03:39,166
So, Yasotharavadi
was able to easily seize Asoraya.

1274
02:03:39,458 --> 02:03:42,833
The villagers at Kung Raga

1275
02:03:42,916 --> 02:03:48,416
were the last group
that fought to the death.

1276
